2026-05-17 21:15:29 | INFO | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Executing: execute_ideal({"code": "# intent: Load worldcities.csv, filter for Western (lng < 0) and Southern (lat < 0) hemispheres, convert population to numeric, find the city with max population and print its city name, country, lat, lng, and population.\nimport pandas as pd\n\n# Load CSV from s3 via provided s3_uri\ns3_uri = 'datagov/kramabench-archeology-easy-6/files/worldcities.csv'\n# pandas can read directly from the s3 path only if aws creds are configured; instead use the file path via DOWNLOAD_MANIFEST if available. \n# However execute_ideal in this environment can read via the s3_uri path provided by the tool (it supports dataset_id/file_path).\n\ndf = pd.read_csv('datagov/kramabench-archeology-easy-6/files/worldcities.csv')\n# Convert lat/lng and population\nfor c in ['lat','lng','population']:\n    df[c] = pd.to_numeric(df[c], errors='coerce')\n\n# Filter Western hemisphere (lng < 0) and Southern hemisphere (lat < 0)\nmask = (df['lng'] < 0) & (df['lat'] < 0)\nsubset = df[mask]\n\n# Find the row with max population\nsubset_nonnull = subset.dropna(subset=['population'])\nif len(subset_nonnull)==0:\n    print('NO_MATCH')\nelse:\n    top = subset_nonnull.loc[subset_nonnull['population'].idxmax()]\n    print(top['city'], top['country'], top['lat'], top['lng'], int(top['population']))\n", "intent": "Filter and find most populous city in SW hemisphere", "dataset_id": "kramabench-archeology-easy-6", "file_path": "files/worldcities.csv"})
